&quot;Two wrongs don't make a right, but they do make for interesting news stories&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=devictionmt>DevictionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#628CBC>(4/21/03 10:23:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=576.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Earth and Beyond</span><hr size=1> EA gave away a 10 day free trial to the game a few months back. <br>
<br>
For the first 2 or 3 days I thought &quot;WOW this is really cool!  But really the intrigue was becaue it was new and different.  And amazingly enough that wore off by day 8.<br>
<br>
You can customize the look of your ship, and the look of your toon, but that rarely amounts to a hill of beans as you hardly ever get close enough out in space.  You can mod certain parts of your ship's equiptment as well.  I.E. Armor, Speed, Weapons, Reactor, etc.  Mods can be purchased from players, looted, or gained via quests.<br>
<br>
Seemed very quest oriented (which was nice, considering that's what alot of people still want this game to be about).  And you can actually complete those quests.  So I'd give that a big +.<br>
<br>
However if you prefer to strap in for some space combat, it's lacking severely.  It's a very RPG style combat, with taking turns while just hovering there.  Very reminiscent of a grade school recess fight, both tards just stand there wailing arms until one goes down or a teacher breaks it up.  You have very little selection in anything but &quot;should I attack this salvage droid?&quot;  Once it's on...that's it.  Just walk away and come back to see if you've won.<br>
<br>
They use a exp deficit system where if you die you now owe exp points rather than lose ground.  Which I personally liked.<br>
<br>
There's not alot of interaction in this game.  It's hard to get to know others.  And the real crapper about this game is that  there's a boatload of travel you have to do...all the time.  It's nothing but miles upon miles of warpspeed while picking your nose, sprinkled with a fight or a quest here and there.<br>
<br>
I got to level 13 in 8 days, didnt really end up playing the last 2 of the free trial.  I think that says something.<br>
<br>
If you've played Homeworld and really liked it you'll probably have an affinity to this more than me.  But this game has no real potency or value to add to our nation of Attention Deficit Disorder kids.   <p>Deviction Xue <br>
